BT 1 0 0 1 0 39 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (1. ) Tj /F2 9 Tf (Optimal fever is 40 degC.) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( Fever shifts the W-parameter toward criticality, increasing immune susceptibility chi by 25%) Tj T* (\(from 31.8x at 37 degC to 39.7x at 40 degC\). This improves pathogen detection and discrimination. Above 41 degC, protein) Tj T* (denaturation approaches and the gain reverses. The body's fever setpoint at 40 degC is the W-parameter optimum -- not) Tj T* (arbitrary, not "burning out the infection," but precision tuning of the immune detection system to its maximum sensitivity.) Tj T* ET
